I made a video from this, to clear see what is my problem.
https://youtu.be/wUSwNeDf_4U
At the bottom there are 12 Urho3D::UI::Button, and every Button have a ToolTip.
If I click a Urho3d::UI::Button with left mouse button then the ToolTip is not disappear (however its parent set to invisibile), but if I click with right mouse button then is functional as expected.
Some technical info:
The user can start commands with these Urho3D::UI::Buttons. Every 12 Urho3d::UI::Button is a child of an UIElement. These UIElements stored in a Vector container. After a click, the correct UIElement is set to visible and the others are set to invisible, so the Urho3D::UI::Buttons are changed properly.

`...::RefreshTheIconLine()
    {
        for (int l = 0; l < 10; l++)
        {
            if(l == cmdMajor_) menuVector_[l]->SetVisible(true);
            else menuVector_[l]->SetVisible(false);
        }
    }
`

Currently completely different types have similar names. Beginners can assume that StaticModel and AnimatedModel is childs of Model class. Class "Model" has no information about materials, so we can rename it to "Mesh" to clarify, that is different types. At the same time we can rename StaticModel to Model, because AnimatedModel is child StaticModel

```
    auto node1 = scene_->CreateChild();
    auto model1 = node_->CreateComponent<Model>();
    model1->SetMesh(cache->GetResource<Mesh>("Meshes/Mesh1.msh"));
    model1->SetMaterial(...);

    auto node2 = scene_->CreateChild();
    auto model2 = node_->CreateComponent<AnimatedModel>();
    model2->SetMesh(cache->GetResource<Mesh>("Meshes/Mesh2.msh"));
    model2->SetMaterial(...);
```

